  "instructions": [
    "Bring almond milk to a boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes until reduced by half.",
    "Stir in balsamic vinegar, cinnamon, coconut sugar, and minced garlic. Simmer for another 5-10 minutes or until thickened slightly.",
    "Fold in slivered almonds and blackberries gently to avoid breaking the berries. Season with a pinch of salt if desired.",
    "Transfer mixture into a serving dish and garnish with extra almond slivers if desired."
